### C

*   **[CAD](/Computer-aided_design)** – See [Computer-aided design](/Computer-aided_design).

*   **[CAM](/Computer-aided_manufacturing)** – See [Computer-aided manufacturing](/Computer-aided_manufacturing).

*   **[CAID](/Computer-aided_industrial_design)** – See [Computer-aided industrial design](/Computer-aided_industrial_design).

*   **[Calculator](/Calculator)** – An electronic device for performing [calculations](/Calculation), from basic [arithmetic](/Arithmetic) to complex [mathematics](/Mathematics). Portable, and generally less prone to emotional errors than humans.

*   **[Calculus](/Calculus)** – The mathematical study of continuous change. It’s the language of motion, of growth, of decay.

*   **[Car handling](/Automobile_handling)** – See [Automobile handling](/Automobile_handling).

*   **[Carbon fiber reinforced polymer](/Carbon_fiber_reinforced_polymer)** – (CFRP) A strong, lightweight [fiber-reinforced plastic](/Fiber-reinforced_plastic) made with [carbon fibers](/Carbon_fibers). It combines the properties of its constituents for superior performance.

*   **[Carbon fibers](/Carbon_fibers)** – Fibers primarily composed of [carbon](/Carbon) atoms, known for their high stiffness, tensile strength, low weight, and resistance to heat and chemicals. They're valuable in demanding applications, though costly.

*   **[Classical mechanics](/Classical_mechanics)** – The physics of macroscopic objects. It describes the motion of everything from [projectiles](/Projectile) to [planets](/Planets). The foundational mechanics before the quantum realm intruded.

*   **[Clean room design](/Clean_room_design)** – A method of recreating a design by [reverse engineering](/Reverse_engineering) without infringing on [copyrights](/Copyright). It's about independent invention, a way to build something similar without stepping on legal toes.

*   **[Clevis fastener](/Clevis_fastener)** – A U-shaped bracket with a pin passing through it, used to connect or secure parts. Simple, effective, and widely used.

*   **[Clock](/Clock)** – An instrument for measuring and indicating [time](/Time). An ancient invention, essential for organizing human activity.

*   **[Clutch](/Clutch)** – A mechanical device that engages and disengages the transmission of [power](/Power_(physics)) between rotating shafts. It’s the intermediary, the control point for power flow.

*   **[CNC](/Numerical_control)** – (Computer Numerical Control) The automated control of [machining](/Machining) tools by [computer](/Computer). It allows for precise, programmed manufacturing without constant human intervention.

*   **[Coefficient of thermal expansion](/Coefficient_of_thermal_expansion)** – A measure of how much the size of an object changes with temperature. It quantifies the material's response to heat.

*   **[Coil spring](/Coil_spring)** – A helical spring made of [elastic](/Elasticity_(physics)) material. Used to store and release energy, absorb shock, or maintain force. It returns to its original shape when unloaded.

*   **[Combustion](/Combustion)** – A high-temperature, exothermic [chemical reaction](/Chemical_reaction) between a [fuel](/Fuel) and an [oxidant](/Oxidant), usually oxygen. It produces heat, light, and byproducts like [smoke](/Smoke).

*   **[Composite material](/Composite_material)** – A material made from two or more constituent materials with different properties. When combined, they create a new material with characteristics superior to the individual components. It's the synergy of materials.

*   **[Compression ratio](/Compression_ratio)** – The ratio of the volume of a [combustion chamber](/Combustion_chamber) at its largest to its smallest capacity. A key specification for internal and external [combustion engines](/Internal_combustion_engine).

*   **[Compressive strength](/Compressive_strength)** – A material's ability to withstand [loads](/Structural_load) that tend to reduce its size, as opposed to [tensile strength](/Ultimate_tensile_strength). It resists being squeezed.

*   **[Computational fluid dynamics](/Computational_fluid_dynamics)** – (CFD) A branch of [fluid mechanics](/Fluid_mechanics) that uses [numerical analysis](/Numerical_analysis) and [computers](/Computer) to simulate and solve problems involving [fluid flows](/Fluid_dynamics). It’s the digital modeling of liquids and gases in motion.

*   **[Computer](/Computer)** – A device that can be instructed to perform sequences of [arithmetic](/Arithmetic) or [logical](/Boolean_algebra) operations automatically. The heart of modern automation and information processing.

*   **[Computer-aided design](/Computer-aided_design)** – (CAD) The use of [computer systems](/Computer_system) to assist in the creation, modification, analysis, and optimization of [designs](/Design). It enhances productivity and improves the quality of design documentation.

*   **[Computer-aided industrial design](/Computer-aided_industrial_design)** – (CAID) A subset of [CAD](/Computer-aided_design) focused on the aesthetic and functional aspects of a product’s look-and-feel.

*   **[Computer-aided manufacturing](/Computer-aided_manufacturing)** – (CAM) The use of software to control [machine tools](/Machine_tool) and other manufacturing equipment. It streamlines the production process.

*   **[Computer numerical control](/Numerical_control)** – (NC, CNC) The automated control of [machining](/Machining) tools by [computer](/Computer) instructions. It’s about programmed precision.

*   **[Conservation of mass](/Conservation_of_mass)** – The principle that in a [closed system](/Closed_system), [mass](/Mass) cannot be created or destroyed, only changed in form. It remains constant over time. A fundamental law.

*   **[Constant-velocity joint](/Constant-velocity_joint)** – (CV joint) A mechanical coupling that allows a [drive shaft](/Drive_shaft) to transmit power through a variable angle at a constant rotational speed. Essential for modern front-wheel drive vehicles.

*   **[Constraint](/Constraint_algorithm_(mechanics))** – (This entry is rather sparse, which is… typical. Constraints are the limitations, the boundaries that dictate how systems can behave.)

*   **[Continuum mechanics](/Continuum_mechanics)** – A branch of [mechanics](/Mechanics) that treats materials as continuous masses, rather than discrete particles. It’s used to analyze the behavior of deformable solids and fluids.

*   **[Control theory](/Control_theory)** – A field of study focused on controlling [dynamical systems](/Dynamical_system) using feedback. It aims for optimal control without delay or overshoot, ensuring [stability](/Stability_theory).

*   **[Corrosion](/Corrosion)** – The gradual destruction of materials, usually [metals](/Metal), through chemical or electrochemical reactions with their environment. It’s the inevitable decay, the return to a more stable form.

*   **[Cotter pin](/Split_pin)** – A pin or wedge used to secure parts by passing through a hole. A simple, yet effective, fastening method.

*   **[Crankshaft](/Crankshaft)** – A mechanical component that converts [reciprocating motion](/Reciprocating_motion) into [rotational motion](/Rotational_motion), or vice versa. It's the heart of many engines.

*   **[Cybernetics](/Cybernetics)** – (This entry is also remarkably brief. Cybernetics is the study of control and communication in animals and machines. It’s about feedback loops, about systems regulating themselves. Perhaps too complex for a simple definition.)

