### D

*   **[Damping ratio](/Damping_ratio)** – A measure of how oscillations in a system die down over time. It quantifies the dissipation of energy. Too little damping, and it oscillates wildly; too much, and it’s sluggish.

*   **[Deformation (engineering)](/Deformation_(engineering))** – The change in size or shape of an object under stress. [Elastic deformation](/Elasticity_(physics)) is reversible; [plastic deformation](/Plasticity_(physics)) is permanent. It’s the material’s response to force.

*   **[Delamination](/Delamination)** – A failure mode where a material fractures into layers. Common in [composites](/Composite_material) and [laminates](/Lamination). It’s the separation of the whole.

*   **[Design](/Design)** – (Another surprisingly brief entry. Design is the blueprint, the plan, the conceptualization of an object or system. It’s where intention meets form.)

*   **[Design for manufacturability](/Design_for_manufacturability)** – (DFM) The practice of designing products to be easily and cost-effectively manufactured. It’s about building with production in mind from the outset.

*   **[Diesel engine](/Diesel_engine)** – An [internal combustion engine](/Internal_combustion_engine) where ignition occurs due to the heat generated by [adiabatic compression](/Adiabatic_compression) of air. Named after [Rudolf Diesel](/Rudolf_Diesel).

*   **[Differential](/Differential_(mechanics))** – A gear train where the speed of one shaft is the average of the speeds of others. Crucial for allowing wheels to rotate at different speeds during a turn.

*   **[Dimensionless number](/Dimensionless_number)** – A quantity with no physical dimensions, often used in [physics](/Physics) and [engineering](/Engineering) to simplify complex relationships. Examples include Reynolds number and Mach number.

*   **[Diode](/Diode)** – A two-[terminal](/Terminal_(electronics)) [electronic component](/Electronic_component) that conducts [current](/Electric_current) primarily in one direction. It’s a one-way street for electricity.

*   **[Diode laser](/Diode_laser)** – (A brief mention, suggesting a laser based on a semiconductor diode.)

*   **[Docking sleeve](/Docking_sleeve)** – (No definition provided. Likely a component used for coupling or connecting.)

*   **[Drafting](/Technical_drawing)** – See [Technical drawing](/Technical_drawing).

*   **[Drifting](/Drifting_(motorsport))** – (A motorsport term, referring to a specific driving technique. Not a core mechanical engineering term, but a related application.)

*   **[Driveshaft](/Driveshaft)** – A component that transmits [torque](/Torque) and rotation between parts that are separated or need to move relative to each other.

*   **[Dynamics (mechanics)](/Dynamics_(mechanics))** – The branch of [classical mechanics](/Classical_mechanics) concerned with the study of [forces](/Force_(physics)) and their effects on [motion](/Motion_(physics)). It's about what makes things move.

*   **[Dynamometer](/Dynamometer)** – A device for measuring [torque](/Torque) and [rotational speed](/Rotational_speed) to calculate the [power](/Power_(physics)) output of an engine or motor. It quantifies performance.

