### E

*   **[Elasticity](/Elasticity_(physics))** – The ability of a material to resist [deformation](/Deformation_(engineering)) and return to its original shape when the applied forces are removed. It’s the inherent springiness of matter.

*   **[Electric current](/Electric_current)** – A stream of [charged particles](/Charged_particles), usually electrons, moving through a conductor. It’s the flow of electrical charge.

*   **[Electric motor](/Electric_motor)** – An [electrical machine](/Electric_machine) that converts [electrical energy](/Electrical_energy) into [mechanical energy](/Mechanical_energy). It uses magnetic fields and [electric current](/Electric_current) to generate rotation.

*   **[Electrical engineering](/Electrical_engineering)** – The discipline concerned with the study, design, and application of equipment and systems that use electricity, electronics, and electromagnetism.

*   **[Electrical circuit](/Electrical_circuit)** – A closed loop that allows [electric current](/Electric_current) to flow.

*   **[Electrical network](/Electrical_network)** – An interconnection of [electrical components](/Electronic_component) or a model thereof.

*   **[Electromagnetism](/Electromagnetism)** – (A fundamental force, the interplay of electricity and magnetism. Its definition here is conspicuously absent, which is… disappointing.)

*   **[Electronic circuit](/Electronic_circuit)** – A circuit composed of individual [electronic components](/Electronic_component) connected by conductive pathways.

*   **[Electronics](/Electronics)** – (The field dealing with electronic circuits and devices. Its definition here is also missing, which feels like an oversight.)

*   **[Energy](/Energy)** – (The fundamental capacity to do work. Its definition is elided, leaving a gaping hole in the foundational concepts.)

*   **[Engine](/Engine)** – (The device that converts energy into mechanical work. Its own definition is absent. Remarkable.)

*   **[Engineering](/Engineering)** – The application of [scientific principles](/Scientific_method) to design and build structures, machines, and other items. It’s about practical application.

*   **[Engineering cybernetics](/Engineering_cybernetics)** – (The application of cybernetic principles to engineering problems. Again, a surprisingly brief mention.)

*   **[Engineering drawing](/Engineering_drawing)** – A [technical drawing](/Technical_drawing) that communicates design information, including [dimensions](/Dimensions) and [tolerances](/Engineering_tolerance). It’s a visual language for construction.

*   **[Engineering economics](/Engineering_economics)** – The study of how to make engineering decisions regarding the allocation of limited resources. A practical application of [microeconomics](/Microeconomic_theory).

*   **[Engineering ethics](/Engineering_ethics)** – The examination of the obligations of [engineers](/Engineer) to society, clients, and the profession. It’s about responsibility.

*   **[Engineering management](/Engineering_management)** – The combination of technical expertise and management skills to oversee complex engineering operations.

*   **[Engineering society](/Engineering_society)** – A [professional organization](/Professional_organization) for [engineers](/Engineer). They provide community, resources, and standards.

*   **[Exploratory engineering](/Exploratory_engineering)** – The process of designing and analyzing hypothetical systems that might be feasible in the future, pushing the boundaries of current technology. It’s about envisioning what *could* be.

