### G

*   **[Gas compressor](/Gas_compressor)** – A device that increases the pressure of a gas by reducing its volume.

*   **[Gauge](/Gauge_(engineering))** – A measuring instrument for determining the size or amount of something.

*   **[Gear](/Gear)** – A rotating mechanical component with teeth that mesh with another toothed part to transmit [torque](/Torque) and alter speed. It’s a fundamental element of power transmission.

*   **[Gear coupling](/Gear_coupling)** – A mechanical device that connects two shafts, allowing for misalignment while transmitting [torque](/Torque).

*   **[Gear ratio](/Gear_ratio)** – The ratio of the pitch circles of mating gears, determining the speed and [mechanical advantage](/Mechanical_advantage) of the gear set.

*   **[Granular material](/Granular_material)** – (Blank. Refers to materials composed of discrete macroscopic particles, like sand or powders.)

