### H

*   **[Heat engine](/Heat_engine)** – A system that converts heat or [thermal energy](/Thermal_energy) into [mechanical energy](/Mechanical_energy). It's the basis of most power generation.

*   **[Heat transfer](/Heat_transfer)** – The movement of [thermal energy](/Thermal_energy) from one system to another.

*   **[Heating and cooling systems](/HVAC)** – Systems designed to control the temperature, humidity, and purity of the air in an enclosed space.

*   **[Hinge](/Hinge)** – A mechanism that allows a part to pivot around a fixed point.

*   **[Hoberman mechanism](/Hoberman_mechanism)** – (Blank. Likely a specific type of expanding or retracting mechanism.)

*   **[Hobson's joint](/Hobson%27s_joint)** – (Blank. Possibly a type of universal joint or coupling.)

*   **[Hooke's law](/Hooke%27s_law)** – The principle that the [force](/Force) needed to extend or compress a spring by some amount is proportional to that distance. It describes [elasticity](/Elasticity_(physics)).

