### O

*   **[Ohm's law](/Ohm%27s_law)** – The relationship between [voltage](/Voltage), [current](/Electric_current), and [resistance](/Electrical_resistance) in an electrical circuit. V = IR.

*   **Orientation** – (Blank. Refers to the position or direction of an object.)

*   **[Overdrive](/Overdrive_(mechanics))** – A gear ratio where the output shaft rotates faster than the input shaft, typically used to reduce engine speed at higher road speeds.

